(FIRST INSTALLATION) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(PURPOSE) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(This repository is the starting point for building the Crypto Wallet Intelligence and) Tj T*
(Paper Trading App in OpenClaw.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(You have a clean Ubuntu 24.04 computer with OpenClaw installed and ChatGPT connected.) Tj T*
(Nothing else is assumed to be installed.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The first objective is to get the project into GitHub, configure OpenClaw with the) Tj T*
(project memory and prompts, install PostgreSQL, install Ollama with qwen3:4b, and add) Tj T*
(Anthropic as the fallback paid model.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(WHAT THIS PACKAGE CONTAINS) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md - the staged development plan OpenClaw should manage.) Tj T*
(- memory/ - project memory files to give OpenClaw long-term context.) Tj T*
(- agents/ - agent role files for compartmentalised development.) Tj T*
(- docs/openclaw-prompts/ - prompts for kickoff, reinstall, setup and maintenance.) Tj T*
(- docs/source/ - source documents for guides and audit files.) Tj T*
(- docs/pdf/ - generated PDF documents.) Tj T*
(- security/asvs/ - ASVS audit templates and control register.) Tj T*
(- backup/ - backup and restore scripts.) Tj T*
(- backend/ - FastAPI backend skeleton.) Tj T*
(- frontend/ - React + Vite frontend skeleton.) Tj T*
(- workers/ - background worker foundation.) Tj T*
(- database/ - migration and seed foundations.) Tj T*
(- .env.example - environment variable template.) Tj T*
(- docker-compose.yml - initial PostgreSQL Docker Compose file.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(FIRST STEPS) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. EXTRACT THE PACKAGE) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Copy the zip file to your Ubuntu computer and extract it:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(bash) Tj T*
(unzip openclaw_crypto_wallet_intelligence_starter.zip) Tj T*
(cd openclaw_crypto_wallet_intelligence_starter) Tj T*
() Tj T*
() Tj T*
(2. CREATE A GITHUB REPOSITORY) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Create a new private GitHub repository, then push this starter package into it.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Example:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
ET
endstream
endobj
